24// structure represents one image definition of a texture created by glTexImage* call.
25struct ImageDefinitionMtl
26{
27 mtl::TextureRef image;
28 angle::FormatID formatID = angle::FormatID::NONE;
29};
30

158 // The texture's data is initially initialized and stored in an array
159 // of images through glTexImage*/glCopyTex* calls. During draw calls, the caller must make sure
160 // the actual texture is created by calling this method to transfer the stored images data
161 // to the actual texture.
162 angle::Result ensureTextureCreated(const gl::Context *context);

171 const mtl::Format &getFormat() const { return mFormat; }
172 const mtl::TextureRef &getNativeTexture() const { return mNativeTexture; }

287 // Copy data to texture's per array's slice/cube's face. NOTE: This function doesn't upload
288 // data to 3D texture's z layer. Metal treats 3D texture's z layer & array texture's slice
289 // differently. For array/cube texture, it is only possible to upload to one slice at a time.
290 angle::Result setPerSliceSubImage(const gl::Context *context,
291 int slice,
292 const MTLRegion &mtlArea,
293 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
294 GLenum type,
295 const angle::Format &pixelsAngleFormat,
296 size_t pixelsRowPitch,
297 size_t pixelsDepthPitch,
298 gl::Buffer *unpackBuffer,
299 const uint8_t *pixels,
300 const mtl::TextureRef &image);
301
302 // Convert pixels to suported format before uploading to texture
303 angle::Result convertAndSetPerSliceSubImage(const gl::Context *context,
304 int slice,
305 const MTLRegion &mtlArea,
306 const gl::InternalFormat &internalFormat,
307 GLenum type,
308 const angle::Format &pixelsAngleFormat,
309 size_t pixelsRowPitch,
310 size_t pixelsDepthPitch,
311 gl::Buffer *unpackBuffer,
312 const uint8_t *pixels,
313 const mtl::TextureRef &image);
314
315 angle::Result generateMipmapCPU(const gl::Context *context);
316
317 mtl::Format mFormat;
318 SurfaceMtl *mBoundSurface = nil;
319 // The real texture used by Metal draw calls.
320 mtl::TextureRef mNativeTexture = nil;
321 id<MTLSamplerState> mMetalSamplerState = nil;
322
323 // Number of slices
324 uint32_t mSlices = 1;
325
326 // Stored images array defined by glTexImage/glCopy*.
327 // Once the images array is complete, they will be transferred to real texture object.
328 // NOTE:
329 // - The second dimension is indexed by configured base level + actual native level
330 // - For Cube map, there will be at most 6 entries in the map table, one for each face. This is
331 // because the Cube map's image is defined per face & per level.
332 // - For other texture types, there will be only one entry in the map table. All other textures
333 // except Cube map has texture image defined per level (all slices included).
334 // - These three variables' second dimension are indexed by image index (base level included).
335 std::map<int, gl::TexLevelArray<ImageDefinitionMtl>> mTexImageDefs;
336 std::map<int, gl::TexLevelArray<RenderTargetMtl>> mPerLayerRenderTargets;
337 std::map<int, gl::TexLevelArray<mtl::TextureRef>> mImplicitMSTextures;
338
339 // Mipmap views are indexed by native level (ignored base level):
340 mtl::NativeTexLevelArray mNativeLevelViews;
341
342 // The swizzled view used for shader sampling.
343 mtl::TextureRef mNativeSwizzleSamplingView;
344
345 GLuint mCurrentBaseLevel = 0;
346 GLuint mCurrentMaxLevel = 1000;
347
348 bool mIsPow2 = false;
349};
